  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Eye symptoms of tearing, redness and itch frequently occur in patients with allergic rhinitis
      or hayfever. The purpose of this study is to learn whether placing allergen (the substance
      that causes allergies) in the nose several days in a row will cause an increase in eye
      symptoms and whether receiving a nasal steroid spray will prevent these eye symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
